  "response_text": "The commercial takes place inside a small grocery store, with crowded shelves, refrigerated cases, produce displays, and handwritten sale signs in the background. It opens on Mr. Whipple, a middle-aged to older man with a balding head, dark hair at the sides, round glasses worn low on his nose, and a white grocer’s coat with a black bow tie. He peeks around the edge of a store display, partly hidden behind shelves of boxed goods, looking alert and concerned as if watching someone off to his left.\n\nA tall man dressed like a Western cowboy stands elsewhere in the store. He wears a wide cream-colored cowboy hat, a red-brown shirt, a black vest with decorative buttons, a neckerchief, and Western-style trousers. He holds a coiled rope or lasso in his hands. Around him are grocery shelves and bins, including a large pink price sign overhead. Mr. Whipple steps into view beside him and gestures outward, apparently pointing toward the trouble he wants stopped. The cowboy smiles, then raises one hand and begins to speak or gesture broadly, taking on the role of a forceful helper.\n\nThe attention shifts to two women standing in front of a large stacked display of Charmin bathroom tissue. Behind them is a big white sign with bold black lettering that reads, “PLEASE DON’T SQUEEZE THE CHARMIN.” The display is made of many white Charmin packages, each showing a baby’s face and the large blue “Charmin” name. The woman on the left is blonde, with a short bouffant hairstyle, wearing a tan coat or vest over a patterned scarf and carrying a handbag. The woman on the right has dark hair styled in a rounded 1960s shape and wears a bright pink cardigan over a black-and-white striped dress or top with a dark collar. Both women hold Charmin packages close to their chests and look pleased and absorbed by them.\n\nBack with the cowboy and Mr. Whipple, the cowboy raises his arm and rope as if issuing a warning. Mr. Whipple stands beside him, shorter and stockier, watching. The cowboy makes large sweeping gestures with the lasso, and Mr. Whipple ducks slightly as the rope or motion passes near him. The two women react with surprise. The brunette in the pink cardigan lifts both arms high, her mouth open, while still holding or releasing a white Charmin package or roll near her hand. The blonde turns her head away, startled, clutching her package and handbag. The sign behind them remains clearly visible over the stack of Charmin.\n\nThe cowboy then strides forward through the store, rope in hand, looking serious. The women appear in a closer view, now with anxious or defensive expressions. The brunette holds up her gloved hands, palms partly open, as if explaining herself, while the blonde glances sideways. The brunette turns back toward the Charmin display and presses or pats one of the packages, then smiles broadly. The blonde also softens into a smile, looking satisfied. The brunette lifts a package from the display and presents it toward the front, beaming. The women’s expressions suggest that the softness of the product is the reason they cannot resist handling it.\n\nA large view of the Charmin package fills the scene. It is a white, soft-looking wrapped pack with a baby’s face printed on the front. The large blue word “Charmin” dominates the bottom, and smaller text near the top left reads “Discover Squeezable softness.” Gloved hands hold the package on both sides and press inward, visibly squeezing the soft bundle so the wrapper dents and gives under the pressure. The product is shown as thick, cushiony, and yielding to the hands.\n\nThe cowboy is then seen holding or looking toward a Charmin package near his chest. He smiles at first, then his expression shifts to a more thoughtful, slightly restrained look. Mr. Whipple stands beside him, holding a Charmin pack himself and pointing with one finger as if reminding him of the rule. The two men face each other in the store aisle, surrounded by stacked goods and signs. The cowboy